==English==

===Pronunciation===
* [[IPA]] /'dεðmætč/

===Etymology===
Presumably first used in [[w:id Software|id Software's]] ''Doom'', which used the word to present an available style of networked game play; networked games were uncommon before ''Doom''.

===Noun===
# A computer game mode found in [[first-person shooter]]s. The players are not on teams, but instead try to [[frag]] as many other players as possible.

===Verb===
# Play a deathmatch.